article.headline: Marquette 81, Nebraska 62
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Travis Diener scored 32 points, including seven 3-pointers, to lead Marquette to an 81-62 victory over Nebraska Tuesday night. Diener scored 20 points in the first half, as the Golden Eagles (10-1) responded from their first loss of the season to Arizona on Saturday. Marquette used a 25-6 run over a nearly 10-minute stretch spanning both halves to put Nebraska away early. The Cornhuskers (4-4) got no closer than eight after halftime. Diener, who was 5-of-17 from the field in the 48-43 defeat against Arizona, scored Marquette's first 12 points on four 3-pointers and sank his first five field goal attempts to help Marquette open the 41-33 halftime lead. The Golden Eagles started the second half on a 10-2 run and led by as many as 25 in the second half. They made 12-of-26 3-pointers for the game. They also outrebounded Nebraska 44-23, even though the Cornhuskers entered play outrebounding their opponents by 12 on average. Marcus Jackson led Marquette with 11 rebounds. Diener made 7-of-11 3 pointers and 8-of-15 shots overall. He finished two points shy of his career high of 34, which came in the Golden Eagles' 69-65 victory over Air Force Nov. 16. Joe Chapman added 14 points for Marquette. Steve Novak had 12. Joe McCray led Nebraska with 17 points, and Aleks Maric and Wes Wilkinson added 12 points each. Starting Nebraska guard Jason Dourisseau, who averages 10.9 points and 6.9 rebounds a game, did not play due to illness. Freshman guard Niv Berkowitz, an Israeli who gained his eligibility this week, played the final 2:12 in his Marquette debut. He replaced Diener, who left to a standing ovation.
